(54, 'en', 'Bananas', 'bananas', 49, 81, '/upload/images/Product/chuoinai.jpg', '', '<p>Raucuqua.net specializes in providing order products for restaurants and hotels of foods that are safe, quality, fast and on time delivery.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Banana is one of the clean fruits that contain a lot of fiber and acrid taste. This fruit has the ability to help remove fats, clean the intestines as well as other impurities in the body, so it is quite nutritious. The information about green bananas as well as notes during use will be shared with you shortly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nutritional value in the composition of green bananas<br />\r\nResearch experts said that the composition of old green bananas contains quite high levels of nutrients. Specifically, in 100 grams of green bananas, there are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Water 74.91g; energy 89 calories, protein 1.09g; fat 0.03g; carbohydrates 22.84g; fiber 2.6g; sugar 12.23g.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Calcium 5mg; phosphorus 22mg; iron 0.26mg; potassium 358mg; zinc 0.15mg; sodium 1mg.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vitamin C content 8.7mg, vitamin A 64 IU; VTM E 0.1mg; VTM K 0.5mg, VTM B6 0.67mg.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Thiamine 0.031mg; riboflavin 0.073mg; niacin 0.665mg, folate 20mg.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'SP0054', 100000, NULL, 0, 0, 'g', '[49]', 'W1siMSJdLFsiMiJdLFtbIjciXV1d', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '{\"weight\":null,\"length\":null,\"width\":null,\"height\":null}', '2022-12-07 09:19:17', '2022-12-15 08:48:34', 7, 7),
(55, 'en', 'Sour tamarind', 'sour-tamarind', 49, 81, '/upload/images/Product/mechua.jpg', '', '<p>Raucuqua.net specializes in providing order products for restaurants and hotels of foods that are safe, quality, fast and on time delivery.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sour tamarind is used as a spice in dishes such as sour soup. In addition, the nutrients in tamarind also bring a lot of very good nutrients to the body such as: reducing fat, preventing anemia, high blood pressure, ..</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Nutritional value of sour tamarind juice</strong><br />\r\nSour tamarind juice contains fiber, protein, minerals such as phosphorus, magnesium, potassium, iron, ....<br />\r\nIn 100g of squeezed sour tamarind, there are about 164 Kcal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The effect of sour tamarind juice on health</strong><br />\r\nSour tamarind has the effect of reducing fat, preventing anemia, high blood pressure, ...</p>', 'SP0055', 100000, NULL, 0, 0, 'g', '[49]', 'W1siMSJdLFsiMiJdLFtbIjciXV1d', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '{\"weight\":null,\"length\":null,\"width\":null,\"height\":null}', '2022-12-07 09:20:28', '2022-12-15 08:48:46', 7, 7),
(56, 'en', 'Red galangal root', 'red-galangal-root', 49, 81, '/upload/images/Product/riengdo.jpg', '', '<p>Raucuquachaua.com specializes in providing order products for restaurants and hotels with safe, quality foods, fast and on-time delivery.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Red galangal (Lesser Galangal) has the scientific name Alpinia Officinarum Hance. In Vietnam, red galangal is also known by other names such as medicinal galangal, luong Khuong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Galangal is a large genus of plants, with less than 230 species and belonging to the Ginger family (Zingiberaceae). Red galangal is a species of plant in the galangal genus, believed to have originated in China.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Red galangal is considered a precious medicine that grows popularly in the Northwest region of our country. Red galangal root can be used as a spice and medicine. However, today not everyone knows all the benefits of this root.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Chemical composition of red galangal root<br />\r\nIn galangal root, there are from 0.5 to 1% of camphor essential oil. The oil itself is a bit viscous, mainly containing xineola and methylxinnamate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Besides essential oil, galangal also contains some of the following substances:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The oily substance that has a spicy taste is called galangola.<br />\r\n0.1% three crystals are tasteless flavone derivatives. These three substances are galangin, alpine and kaempfert.</p>', 'SP0056', 150000, NULL, 0, 0, 'g', '[49]', 'W1siMSJdLFsiMiJdLFtbIjciXV1d', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '{\"weight\":null,\"length\":null,\"width\":null,\"height\":null}', '2022-12-07 09:21:46', '2022-12-15 08:49:00', 7, 7),
(57, 'en', 'Turmeric', 'turmeric', 49, 81, '/upload/images/Product/cunghe.jpg', '', '<p>Raucuquachaua.com specializes in providing order products for restaurants and hotels with safe, quality foods, fast and on-time delivery.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Origin of golden turmeric</strong><br />\r\nIt is native to tropical Tamil Nadu, southeastern India, and needs temperatures between 20 degrees Celsius and 30 degrees Celsius (68 degrees Fahrenheit and 86 degrees Fahrenheit) and a significant amount of annual rainfall to thrive. . Plants are harvested annually for their tubers, and propagated from a portion of them the following season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">India is the main producer of turmeric. Turmeric is widely grown in South Asia and Southeast Asia. They have many different regional names depending on the language and country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Preserve</strong><br />\r\nWhen not used immediately, the tubers are boiled for 30 to 45 minutes and then dried in a hot oven. They are then ground into a dark orange-yellow powder. Turmeric powder is often used as a spice in Tamil cuisine, curries. It is also used to dye and color mustards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Active ingredient curcumin</strong><br />\r\nIts active ingredient is curcumin with a slightly hot, slightly bitter, mustard-like taste. Curcumin &nbsp;‘ears the taste of the earth’ in a different way. Curcumin is the center of attraction because of its potential healing properties. It works for a number of conditions, including cancer, Alzheimer\'s, diabetes, allergies, arthritis, and other chronic conditions.</p>', 'SP0057', 20000, NULL, 0, 0, 'g', '[49]', 'W1siMSJdLFsiMiJdLFtbIjciXV1d', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '{\"weight\":null,\"length\":null,\"width\":null,\"height\":null}', '2022-12-07 09:22:57', '2022-12-15 08:49:14', 7, 7),
(58, 'en', 'Asparagus', 'asparagus', 50, 81, '/upload/images/Product/mangtay.jpg', '', '<p>Raucuquachaua.com specializes in providing order products for restaurants and hotels with safe, quality foods, fast and on-time delivery.</p>', '<p><strong>EFFECTS OF Asparagus</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Provides many nutrients but very few calories</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The calories in asparagus are very low, but they have an impressive amount of nutrients. Like protein, or fat, along with vitamins and minerals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asparagus is an excellent source of vitamin K. An important nutrient that improves bone health and prevents blood clotting in patients with thrombosis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>It is a very good source of antioxidants</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asparagus contains many of the same antioxidants as some other green vegetables. These include vitamin E, vitamin C, as well as various flavonoids and polyphenols.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These substances have been found to have antihypertensive, anti-inflammatory, antiviral, and anticancer effects in several human and animal studies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Furthermore, purple asparagus contains pigments called anthocyanins. They give vegetables their vibrant colors. And in particular, the supply of anthocyanins has been shown to slow oxidation, reducing blood pressure and the risk of heart attack.</p>', 'SP0058', 60000, NULL, 0, 0, 'g', '[50]', 'W1siMSJdLFsiMiJdLFtbIjgiXV1d', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '{\"weight\":null,\"length\":null,\"width\":null,\"height\":null}', '2022-12-07 09:24:25', '2022-12-15 08:49:33', 7, 7);
